on and Norman Kings''<ref>{{cite web|title= The Saxon and Norman Kings|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/63447340&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''From Alfred to Henry III 871–1272''<ref>{{cite web|title= From Alfred to Henry III 871–1272|publisher=World Cat |url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/185648057&referer=brief_results}} Accessed on 10 March 2009</ref> * ''Carte Nativorum: A [[Peterborough Abbey]] Cartulary of the Fourteenth Century''<ref>{{cite web|title= Carte nativorum : a Peterborough Abbey cartulary of the fourteenth century|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/185781571&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''The Letters of John of Salisbury''<ref>{{cite web |title= The letters of John of Salisbury|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/48318911&referer=brief_results}} Accessed on 10 March 2009</ref> * ''The Letters of John of Salisbury. Vol. 2, The Later Letters (1163–1180)''<ref>{{cite web|title= The letters of John of Salisbury. Vol. 2, The later letters (1163–1180)|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/186720386&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''A History of [[Gonville and Caius College]]''<ref>{{cite web|title= A history of Gonville and Caius college|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/185477127&referer=brief_results}} Accessed on 10 March 2009</ref> * ''[[Gilbert Foliot]] and his letters''<ref>{{cite web|title= Gilbert Foliot and his letters|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/64512070&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''The Heads of Religious Houses, England and Wales: Volume 1, 940–1216''<ref>{{cite web|title= The heads of religious houses, England and Wales. [1], 940–1216|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/270781519&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''The Investiture Disputes''<ref>{{cite web|title= The investiture disputes|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/221050799&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''Religious Sentiment and Church Design in the Later Middle Ages''<ref>{{cite web|title= Religious sentiment and church design in the later Middle Ages|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/66298679&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''Archbishop Lanfranc, the English Bishops and the Council of London of 1075''<ref>{{cite web|title= Archbishop Lanfranc, the English bishops and the Council of London of 1075|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/49413804&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''The Monastic Constitutions of Lanfranc''<ref>{{cite web|title= The monastic constitutions of Lanfranc|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/48154671&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''Councils and Synods, with Other Documents Relating to the English Church: Volume I: A.D. 871–1204''<ref>{{cite web|title= Councils and synods, with other documents relating to the English church, I, A.D. 871–1204|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/224372669&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> * ''Hugh the chanter : the history of the church of York, 1066–1127''<ref>{{cite web|title= Hugh the chanter : the history of the church of York, 1066–1127|publisher=World Cat|url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/213035056&referer=brief_results |accessdate=10 March 2009 }}</ref> *''Oxford and Cambridge''. Cambridge University Press, 1988 (with [[Roger Highfield]]) {{div col end}}
