[[File:Санкт-Петербург, лев с Адмиралтейской набережной.jpg|thumb|One of the lion sculptures]] The '''Lions at the Dvortsovaya pier''' are two [[lions in art|lion sculptures]] in [[bronze]] placed at the [[Admiralty embankment]] in [[Saint Petersburg]] since 1832. The lions are copies of the late 16th century [[Italy|Italian]] [[Medici lions]] in [[Florence]].
The lions are the best known among several Medici lions and other lion sculptures in Saint Petersburg. The sculptures were created by the German craftsman, [[Johan Gottlieb Prang]] to designs by sculptor [[Ivan Prokofiev]].
